Conclusions\par
\b0 We were able to incorporate air resistance into our problem, but as we saw above this is only one of many external factors affecting an object's motion. Further refining the model would likely be unfeasible using standard mathematics, and we must instead turn to algorithms using \b numerical solutions \b0 that run through all the calculations for us. \par
There is a whole field of study dedicated to the application of these solutions known as \b computational fluid dynamics\b0  (CFD). This field is so complicated that there is a million dollar prize\super [1]\nosupersub  to be won to anyone who can solve a problem related to the fundamental equations governing it, known as the Navier-Stokes equations.\par
In professions such as engineering, where these calculations are applied to important aspects of life such as cars, buildings and bridges, we simply cannot afford to be incorrect, otherwise lives and assets are put at risk. A real engineer would be expected to consider all these influences and much more when implementing their models. While an innocent problem like dropping a ball may look simple enough in class, the maths quickly grows out of hand once the nitty-gritty details of physics in the real world are at play.\par
